The paper deals with routing and scheduling in packet-switched networks, which are topics related to network infrastructure (cs.NI) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses scheduling protocols, which fall under the category of distributed systems (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper mentions the implementation of the algorithm under today's Internet routing paradigms, which is related to network security and information theory (cs.SI, cs.IT).
